snippet.textDisplay: After watching these videos I remembered something from child hood. I remembered a night alone at home hearing what I thought was my mom calling for me, I look around and no one around. Fucked up thing is she wasn’t even in the country.. LOL. Anyways went to sleep and I woke up to pressure on my chest and when I opened my eyes, I saw something red right in my face. Passed back out and when I woke up, I woke up sweating. Never experienced again until after a few years after. Felt pressure, try to call for my parents but felt like something was covering my mouth and couldn’t get help. Later found it was from sleep paralysis, after talking to my parents. So never thought about it again, until just a few weeks ago I felt pressure again this time it wasn’t sleep paralysis but I was actually able to move. I got really mad, and literally force myself up and turn on the light looked around and nothing. So yea my fun experience. So I feel what Corey feels when he doesn’t want to approach it and wants to ignore it. 😂🤷‍♂️

Take a break and learn to be calm and mentally strong , even with the experience you guys have I was surprised you didnt stay for longer.

This cannot be called an investigation imo, I'm sorry but its true.. Did you really investigate anything or did you just open a quija board and played for like 20 minutes and chickened out? I personally think its the latter..

I literally used to scream when these videos would come out but now its just getting boring, its always the same pattern.. You go to a haunted place, hear noises and proceed to leave .. And that is not proving anything to us.

I am rambling, sorry, I've been watching you for years and this is kind of disappointing, to the point that I think you should get back to exploring, or take a break to think this through.😘
